# CSS Modules

- Each component gets a colocated `*.module.css` file.
- Import as `styles` and apply with `className={styles.myClass}`.
- Use **camelCase** class names so they work as JS properties.

# Write Clean CSS

Keep styles simple, readable, and flat. Avoid deep abstractions or over-engineering. Prefer explicit properties over clever shorthands when clarity matters.

# Native CSS Nesting

Use CSS nesting to colocate related styles. Keep nesting shallow (2-3 levels max).

```css
/* ✅ Good — shallow, readable nesting */
.card {
  padding: 1rem;

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  &:hover {
    background: var(--color-surface-hover);
  }
}

/* ❌ Bad — too deep, hard to follow */
.card {
  .header {
    .title {
      span {
        &:hover { ... }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

# Design Tokens

Use CSS custom properties (e.g. `var(--color-text)`, `var(--color-text-muted)`) for colors and spacing instead of hard-coded values, when tokens are available.
